observe.desc:
      [
      {She knew it must have something to do with that Abnormality gripping its nail and hammer.
From the moment she had first joined the corperation, that thing had always been there. However, her first real encounter with it had been only two weeks ago. But truth be told, she had despised that accursed thing from the very beginning! Just looking at it was enough to send a shiver down her spine - let alone the nail in its hand. Oh, the nail! Let visceras come, let blood come, let phantoms and horrors come - she feared none of those! But nails, those horrifying nails, she could not bear them.
She had known it from the very beginning. That nail was destined to pierce her eye, to run straight through her brain. It was inevitable! She had done everything in her power to avoid crossing paths with that thing, just to escape the gnawing sense of dread it stirred within her.
God, let not this innocent girl fall victim to such cruelty!}
      ]

[
{- But it wasn't my fault! What else could I have done? That creature was right there before my eyes - if I hadn't locked the door at that moment, the entire department would have perished! It was the right decision; there was nothing to be afraid of. Even though her face, pressed against the window, had been utterly ghastly, that was simply something I had to deal with myself.}
]

[
{At this thought, Sonya felt reassured. Yes, her decision had been flawless. She had no sin for which to repent.}
]

      [
      {They said that its nail and hammer judged those guilty of sin.
If that was true, then she had nothing to fear.
...}
      ]

      [
      {The vilest curse still lingered on Sonya's lips when the sound of metal hammering rang out from within the Containment Unit.
Scarlet blood smeared across the glass. Sonya's voice was gone.}
      ]
